article.headline: Western Carolina 81, Wofford 75
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Freshman Jake Robinson scored 20 points off the bench, making six of his seven 3-pointers, to help Western Carolina to a 81-75 victory over Wofford on Wednesday night. The Catamounts (4-1, 1-0 Southern Conference) led 77-66 with 1:07 left, but the Terriers (4-4, 0-2) got three 3-pointers in a row to trail by four with 11 seconds left. Antonio Russell then hit a pair of free throws to give Western Carolina the six-point win. The Catamounts led for most of the game and had a 37-23 advantage at halftime. Shane Nichols led all scorers with 24 points, while Eric Marshall added 18 points and Tyler Whatley had 11 points and eight rebounds for Wofford. Antonio Russell had 19 points and Nick Aldridge added 15 points and 10 rebounds for Western Carolina.
